# Cove — project rules

## Tests
- **Tests live in a `__tests__/` folder, never co-located/blended with running code.** Put a module's
  test in a `__tests__/` directory beside it (e.g. `convex/engine/foo.ts` → `convex/engine/__tests__/foo.test.ts`).
  Rationale: keeps source modules free of test code, and `__tests__` starts with `_` so the Convex
  bundler auto-ignores it (like `_generated`) — test files never ship as functions. (vitest still
  discovers `**/__tests__/**/*.test.ts`; tsc still typechecks them via the `convex/**` / `src/**` include.)
- Drive the engine deterministically through the in-process `MockLanguageModelV2` seam
  (`convex/providers/testModel.ts` → reserved model id `cove-test/mock`); never import `ai/test` (it
  statically pulls `msw`, an unshipped devDependency).
- Convex functions can't be unit-tested (no `convex-test` installed); test the pure injectable cores and
  verify the Convex glue via `convex dev --once` + `convex run` (see below).

## Running tools (the `.bin` scripts lack +x — macOS-installed node_modules)
- Typecheck: `node node_modules/typescript/bin/tsc --noEmit` (must exit 0 every change).
- Tests: `node node_modules/vitest/vitest.mjs run [path]`.
- Deploy/codegen/run: `node node_modules/convex/bin/main.js <dev --once | codegen | run | env>`.
  `codegen` only pushes component bindings; `dev --once` is the full deploy that makes functions callable.

## Source conventions
- **Reference-header convention:** every source file opens with a header citing its flue/pi origin file +
  npm package (or `New (Convex backend) · @cove/runtime`), per `docs/design/08`.
- **Naming:** no `Flue`/`Pi` identifiers; brand types are `Cove*`; error-message prefix is `[cove]`.
  Never reference "birdwatch".
- **`"use node"`:** any `convex/*.ts` that imports (transitively) the AI SDK (`ai`/`@ai-sdk/*`),
  `@upstash/box`, or node builtins MUST carry `"use node"` as its first statement. Pure V8-safe modules
  import none of those. Queries/mutations stay box/AI-free; only `"use node"` actions touch the sandbox.
- **Execution boundary (doc 08 §3):** Convex orchestrates + persists; the sandbox executes; the LLM decides.
